= {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Babyface\n}}\n| length10        = 4:33\n\n| title11         = Privacy\n| writer11        = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Jerkins\n*Jerkins III\n*Daniels\n*[[Bernard Belle]]\n}}\n| extra11         = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Jerkins\n}}\n| length11        = 5:05\n\n| title12         = Don't Walk Away\n| writer12        = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Riley\n*Richard Carlton Stites\n*Reed Vertelney\n}}\n| extra12         = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Riley\n}}\n| length12        = 4:25\n\n| title13         = [[Cry (Michael Jackson song)|Cry]]\n| writer13        = [[R. Kelly|Robert Kelly]]\n| extra13         = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Kelly\n}}\n| length13        = 5:01\n\n| title14         = The Lost Children\n| writer14        = Jackson\n| extra14         = Jackson\n| length14        = 4:00\n\n| title15         = Whatever Happens\n| note15          = featuring [[Carlos Santana]]\n| writer15        = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Riley\n}}\n| extra15         = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Riley\n}}\n| length15        = 4:56\n\n| title16         = Threatened\n| writer16        = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Jerkins\n*Jerkins III\n*Daniels\n}}\n| extra16         = {{flat list|\n*Jackson\n*Jerkins\n}}\n| length16        = 4:19\n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n*\"Unbreakable\" features a rap verse by [[The Notorious B.I.G.]] The rap verse was originally from the song \"[[You Can't Stop the Reign (song)|You Can't Stop the Reign]]\" by [[Shaquille O'Neal]]. It was written by Carl McIntosh, Jane Eugene and Steve Nichol.\n*\"Break of Dawn\", \"2000 Watts\" and \"Threatened\" were excluded from the original Chinese release.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u8fc8\u514b\u5c14\u00b7\u6770\u514b\u900aMichael Jackson:\u5929\u4e0b\u65e0\u654cInvincible-\u97f3\u4e50-\u5353\u8d8a\u4e9a\u9a6c\u900a |url=https://www.amazon.cn/dp/B002FL3KCM|publisher=Amazon.cn|accessdate=2011-01-04}}</ref> In the Chinese edition of the [[box set]] ''[[The Collection (Michael Jackson album)|The Collection]]'' released in 2013, all 16 tracks are included.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u8fc8\u514b\u5c14\u2022\u6770\u514b\u900a:\u661f\u5149\u4f20\u5947(5CD) [\u5957\u88c5]|url=https://www.amazon.cn/gp/product/B00C9T6VNK|publisher=Amazon.cn|accessdate=2013-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from ''Invincible'' album liner notes.<ref name=\"linernotes\"/>\n\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Michael Jackson]] \u2013 lead vocals {{small|(all tracks)}}, background vocals {{small|(1-7, 9-12, 15-16)}}, arranger {{small|(8, 14)}}, multiple instruments {{small|(1, 4, 6, 16)}}, programming {{small|(2, 3)}}, drum programming {{small|(4, 13)}}, orchestral arrangements and conducting {{small|(8)}}, keyboard programming {{small|(9, 13, 14)}}\n* [[Marsha Ambrosius]] \u2013 background vocals {{small|(track 7)}}\n* Maxi Anderson \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Gloria Augustus \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]] \u2013 acoustic guitar, bass guitar, background vocals, drum programming, and keyboards {{small|(track 10)}}\n* [[Tom Bahler]] \u2013 youth choir conductor {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Emanuel \u201cBucket\u201d Baker \u2013 drums {{small|(track 11)}}\n* Rose Beatty \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Edie Lehmann Boddicker \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Robert Bolyard \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Norman Jeff Bradshaw - horns {{small|(track 7)}}\n* [[Brandy Norwood|Brandy]] \u2013 additional background vocals {{small|(track 1)}}\n* Stuart Brawley \u2013  whistle solo {{small|(track 15)}}\n* Mary Brown \u2013 additional background vocals {{small|(track 15)}}\n* Tim Brown \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Brad Buxer \u2013 drum programming {{small|(tracks 4, 13)}}, keyboards {{small|(8)}}, keyboard programming {{small|(9, 12, 14)}}\n* [[David Campbell (composer)|David Campbell]] \u2013 string arrangement {{small|(track 11)}}\n* Matt Cappy \u2013 horns {{small|(track 7)}}\n* Martha Cowan \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* [[Andra\u00e9 Crouch]] \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* [[Sandra Crouch]] \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* [[Paulinho da Costa]] \u2013 percussion {{small|(track 13)}}\n* [[LaShawn Daniels]] \u2013 background vocals {{small|(tracks 2, 11)}}\n* Valerie Doby \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* [[Dr. Freeze]] \u2013 background vocals {{small|(tracks 4, 5)}}, multiple instruments {{small|(4)}}\n* Monique Donally \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Kevin Dorsey \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Marja Dozier \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Alfie Silas Durio \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* [[Nathan East]] \u2013 bass guitar {{small|(track 11)}}\n* Jason Edmonds \u2013 choir {{small|(track 10)}}\n* Geary Lanier Faggett \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Vonciele Faggett \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Fats - rap {{small|(tracks 2, 3)}}\n* Lynn Fiddmont-Lindsey \u2013 choir {{small|(track 10)}}\n* Kirstin Fife \u2013 violin {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Judy Gossett \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Harold Green \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Jonathon Hall \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Justine Hall \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* [[Dre & Vidal|Andre Harris]] \u2013 multiple instruments {{small|(track 7)}}\n* Scottie Haskell \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Micha Haupman \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Gerald Heyward \u2013 drums {{small|(track 11)}}\n* Tabia Ivery \u2013 choir {{small|(track 10)}}\n* Luana Jackman \u2013 youth choir {{small|(track 14)}}\n* Prince Jackson \u2013 narrative {{small|(track 14)}}\n* [[Rodney Jerkins]] \u2013 multiple instruments {{small|(1, 4, 6, 16)}}, programming {{small|(2, 3)}}\n* Tenika Johns \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Angela Johnson \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Daniel Johnson \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Zaneta M. Johnson \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* Laquentan Jordan \u2013 vocals {{small|(track 8)}}\n* [[R. Kelly]] \u2013 choir 